  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add onion, carrot, and celery, and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add haddock fillets and cook for 2 minutes on each side, until browned.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together harissa, cumin, smoked paprika, and cayenne pepper.",
    "Add the spice mixture to the Dutch oven and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 10-12 minutes, or until the fish is cooked through.",
    "Stir in lemon juice, if using.",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Garnish with fresh parsley or cilantro, if desired.",
    "Serve hot over couscous or rice.",
    "Adjust seasoning as needed."
